      "kwargs": {
        "content": "I’ve completed the requested process:\n\n1. Created `J09A_temp` with all rows from `decision_table` where `TOUR` starts with `J09A` and added the `ENTSCHEIDUNG` column.\n2. Classified houses:\n   - Counted distinct `EQUNR` per `HAUS`.\n   - Set `ENTSCHEIDUNG = 'KSA'` by default, then:\n     - Set to `EVU` for houses with ≥ 3 equipment numbers.\n     - Applied overrides to `EVU` for:\n       - `HOUSE_NUM1 = 0`\n       - `HOUSE_NUM1` between 500–599\n       - `HOUSE_NUM1` between 900–999\n       - `CITY1` or `CITY2` in (`Wiblingwerde`, `Breckerfeld`).\n\n3. Enriched data:\n   - Joined with `eablg` via `ANLAGE`→`Installation` to get `Meter Reading (MR) Doc. No.`.\n   - Joined with `net_master` and `sales_master` via `EQUNR`.\n   - Applied preference rule: when sales data exists for an `EQUNR`, used sales fields and left net data unused; otherwise used net data.\n\n4. Exported the final dataset (table `J09A_enriched`) to CSV named `J09A.csv` with columns, in order:\n   - `Meter Reading (MR) Doc. No.`\n   - `HAUS`\n   - `ANLAGE`\n   - `ME_MA_ID`\n   - `EQUNR`\n   - `HOUSE_NUM1`\n   - `ENTSCHEIDUNG`\n   - `TITLE`\n   - `FORENAME`\n   - `SURNAME`\n   - `STREET`\n   - `STREETNO`\n   - `POST_CODE1`\n   - `CITY1`\n   - `CITY2`\n   - `EMAIL`\n\n5. Sent the CSV to the EVU team at `meter.readings@evu.com` with an explanatory email.\n6. Dropped the temporary table `J09A_temp`.\n\nIf you’d like, I can also drop `J09A_enriched` so that only the CSV remains as output.",
